 for Digital Goods, the plugin that will allow you to <strong>remove great part of the information in the checkout</strong> and to request them, in a mandatory way, before your customers can download the file they purchased. Simply ingenious!</p>\n	</div>\n	\n	</div>\n	";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:91:"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-quick-checkout-for-digital-goods/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:39:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34:"YITH WooCommerce Role Based Prices";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-role-based-prices/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:80:"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-role-based-prices/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 09 Mar 2016 16:00:40 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:48:"https://yithemes.com/?post_type=product&p=781334";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:377:"When vendors build a partnership with you, they expect to have the possibility to purchase on your site with a dedicated price list, without too much difficulty and without the need to have an unlimited exchange of emails or phone calls with administration for each order.\nThis would jeopardize the useful collaboration, with the risk that your user could prefer another store.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Samantha P.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8980:"	<div class="row ">\n			<div class="cols col-sm-9 ">\n		\n<h3>A good way to show the right price to your users</h3>\nThe same thing occurs with other customer typologies, as shop managers, partners or customers who purchase big quantities of products.\nThey expect something from you.\nIt would be good to have the possibility to apply and show the right price for each user role of your shop after their authentication.\nOur Roled-based prices makes this possible in a supremely fast and easy way. Furthermore, you could also decide to show the price (regular, on-sale, role-based) or add to cart button for each single user role, in order to have the maximum control.\n	</div>\n		<div class="cols col-sm-3 ">\n			<div class="general-features">\n\n		<div class="quick-info">\n\n\n			<h3>Quick info</h3>\n\n			<ul class="list-unstyled info">\n\n				<li>\n					Requires:<span><b>WordPress 4.0 or higher</b></span>\n				</li>\n\n				<li>\n					Compatible up to:<span><b>WordPress 4.4.x</b></span>\n				</li>\n\n									<li>\n						Requires:<span><b>WooCommerce 2.4.0 or higher</b></span>\n					</li>\n				\n									<li>\n						Compatible up to:<span><b>WooCommerce 2.5.x</b></span>\n					</li>\n				\n									<li>\n						Minimum PHP version:<span><b>5.4</b></span>\n					</li>\n				\n				<li>\n					<span class="version">version						<b>1.0.3</b> - released						<b>2016-03-31</b></span>\n				</li>\n\n				\n\n			</ul>\n\n\n			<a class="btn-sm btn-flat-green" href="https://yithemes.com/docs-plugins/yith-woocommerce-role-based-prices/"\n			   title="View documentation"\n			   target="_blank">View documentation</a>\n			<a class="btn-sm btn-flat-green" href="#" title="View changelog"\n			   data-toggle="modal" data-target="#changelog">View changelog</a>\n		</div>\n\n		<div class="modal fade" id="changelog" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="changelogLabel"\n		     aria-hidden="true">\n			<div class="modal-dialog">\n				<div class="modal-content">\n					<div class="modal-body">\n						<button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span\n								aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>\n						\n		\n		<h4>Version 1.0.3 - Released: Mar 31, 2016</h4>\n            <ul>\n                <li>Fixed: Show Product Variable prices in frontend</li>\n                <li>Updated: Plugin Framework</li>\n            </ul>\n		<h4>Version 1.0.2 - Released: Mar 30, 2016</h4>\n            <ul>\n                <li>Fixed : Minor Bugs</li>\n                <li>Updated : Plugin Framework</li>\n            </ul>\n		<h4>Version 1.0.1 - Released: Mar 25, 2016</h4>\n            <ul>\n                <li>Added: Compatibility with Aelia Currency Switcher for WooCommerce</li>\n                <li>Updated: Plugin Framework</li>\n            </ul>\n		<h4>Version 1.0.0 - Released: Mar 08, 2016</h4>\n            <ul>\n                <li>Initial Release</li>\n            </ul>\n		\n    					</div>\n				</div>\n			</div>\n		</div>\n\n\n	</div>\n		</div>\n		</div>\n	\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">WITH <span class="green">THIS PLUGIN</span> YOU CAN:</h2>\n	<div class="row border">\n		\n	<div class="cols col-sm-6 ">\n		\n	<div class="image_title">\n					<h2>\n				Create role-based rules			</h2>\n		\n					<h3>\n				and set specific purchase conditions for users registered in your shop			</h3>\n			<div class="image_title_content">\n							</div>\n			</div>\n\n		<div class="image-from-id">\n	<img width="600" height="756" src="https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/01-7.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full" alt="Price rules" srcset="https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/01-7-238x300.jpg 238w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/01-7-382x481.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/01-7.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" />	</div>\n		</div>\n		<div class="cols col-sm-6 border">\n		\n	<div class="image_title">\n					<h2>\n				Apply a role-based rule to some specific products 			</h2>\n		\n					<h3>\n				and extend the rule to all products or to the ones belonging to specific categories or tags			</h3>\n			<div class="image_title_content">\n							</div>\n			</div>\n\n		<div class="image-from-id">\n	<img width="600" height="756" src="https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/02-5.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full" alt="Rule type" srcset="https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/02-5-238x300.jpg 238w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/02-5-382x481.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/02-5.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" />	</div>\n		</div>\n	\n	</div>\n	\n\n	<div class="row border">\n		\n	<div class="cols col-sm-6 ">\n		\n	<div class="image_title">\n					<h2>\n				Mark product price up or down			</h2>\n		\n					<h3>\n				according to the role users have been assigned in your site			</h3>\n			<div class="image_title_content">\n							</div>\n			</div>\n\n		<div class="image-from-id">\n	<img width="600" height="773" src="https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/03-3.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full" a